\b 1. Introduction\b0\par
This Test Plan communicates the testing approach for the SupportAI project. It defines the objectives, scope, risks, schedule, test environment, automation strategy, and deliverables for validating the system.\par
\par
\b 1.1 Objectives\b0\par
SupportAI is a web-based support ticketing and routing system with a React frontend and a FastAPI backend backed by SQLite. The objective of testing is to verify that users can log in by role, create and track tickets, allow support agents to resolve assigned tickets, and allow administrators to review tickets and agents. Unit and integration testing are included to validate both isolated logic and end-to-end workflow behavior.\par
\par
Phase 1 focuses on the following must-have outcomes:\par
1. Customer can create a ticket.\par
2. Customer can view created and resolved tickets.\par
3. Support agent can view assigned tickets.\par
4. Support agent can resolve tickets with notes.\par
5. Admin can review all tickets and agent information.\par
\par
