\par
\b 2. Scope\b0\par
In scope:\par
1. Authentication by role: customer, support, admin.\par
2. Ticket creation and retrieval.\par
3. Ticket status tracking and resolution.\par
4. Queue classification, tagging, and assignment logic covered by Jest tests.\par
5. Unit and integration testing of the provided JavaScript test modules.\par
\par
Out of scope:\par
1. Load and stress testing.\par
2. Production deployment validation.\par
3. Migration of legacy documents into the application.\par
\par
\b 3. Assumptions / Risks\b0\par
\b 3.1 Assumptions\b0\par
1. Jest and required dependencies are installed in the frontend workspace.\par
2. The test environment is available locally.\par
3. The provided test data is sufficient for unit and integration coverage.\par
\par
\b 3.2 Risks\b0\par
1. Scope creep may add features not covered by the current test suite.\par
Mitigation: update test cases with each iteration.\par
2. Inline self-contained tests may diverge from the live application code if the product changes.\par
Mitigation: keep the suite synchronized with implementation changes.\par
3. Environment differences may affect repeatability of test execution.\par
Mitigation: standardize Node, Jest, and project dependency versions.\par
\par
\b 4. Test Approach\b0\par
The project follows an iterative approach. Testing will include:\par
1. Unit testing of database helpers, classifiers, tagging, ranking, and assignment logic.\par
2. Integration testing of login, ticket pipeline, assignment behavior, status transitions, and routing consistency.\par
3. Exploratory testing for user-facing workflows where needed.\par
\par
\b 4.1 Test Automation\b0\par
Automated tests are implemented using Jest. The current automated suite includes:\par
1. Unit tests: authentication, transformer engine, priority classifier, queue classifier, type classifier, tag extractor, assignment engine.\par
2. Integration tests: login and session handling, ticket creation pipeline, assignment under load, ticket status transitions, classifier consistency, repeated-problem routing.\par
\par
